label.value: normal growth on myxothiazol

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing myxothiazol.

label.value: sensitive to myxothiazol

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to myxothiazol. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of myxothiazol that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased transcription from HSE promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription from a promoter that contains one or more heat shock elements (HSEs) occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: ectopic CENP-A containing chromatin assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin containing the histone H3 variant CenH3 (also called CENP-A; Cnp1 in S. pombe) are assembled in one or more regions of the chromosome away from the centromere. CENP-A-containing nucleosomes are normally assembled into chromatin at the centromeres, encompassing the central core and centromeric inner repeat regions.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromeric chromatin, with protein mislocalized to nucleoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the nucleoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to sodium chloride

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to sodium chloride. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of sodium chloride that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to calcium ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to calcium ions.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased nuclease activity during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a nuclease activity is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: increased RNA catabolic process during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of an RNA catabolic process is increased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: increased protein level in chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein found associated with chromatin is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromeric chromatin during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is decreased during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is decreased during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is increased during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to centromeric chromatin during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is increased during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal rate of actin filament-based movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin filament-based movement is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Actin filament-based movement is the movement of organelles or other particles along actin filaments, or sliding of actin filaments past each other, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: abnormal actin filament-based movement

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin filament-based movement is abnormal. Actin filament-based movement is the movement of organelles or other particles along actin filaments, or sliding of actin filaments past each other, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: increased rate of actin filament-based movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin filament-based movement is increased. Actin filament-based movement is the movement of organelles or other particles along actin filaments, or sliding of actin filaments past each other, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: decreased rate of actin filament-based movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin filament-based movement is decreased. Actin filament-based movement is the movement of organelles or other particles along actin filaments, or sliding of actin filaments past each other, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: incomplete actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring contraction begins, but stops before the ring completely constricts and is disassembled.

label.value: normal rate of protein exchange in actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of protein exchange in the actomyosin contractile ring is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Normally, proteins including actin and myosin are turned over between the contractile ring and elsewhere in the cytoplasm; exchange is faster during than before ring constriction.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal onset of actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which contractile ring assembly begins at the normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) time relative to other cell cycle events.

label.value: normal onset of actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cgontractile ring contraction begins at the normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) time relative to other cell cycle events.

label.value: normal protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to heat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to heat.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased level of stress responsive gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more messenger RNAs that are normally expressed during a cellular response to stress measured in a cell is lower than normal (i.e. lower than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: abnormal RNA 3'-end processing during cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which formation of the mature 3' end of an RNA molecule is abnormal during a cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to endoplasmic reticulum stress is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of meiotic recombination double-strand break repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the repair of double-strand breaks formed as part of meiotic recombination begins later than normal.

label.value: normal meiosis-specific chromatin remodeling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which chromatin remodeling that occurs as part of meiosis I is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal chromatin remodeling during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which chromatin remodeling that occurs as part of meiosis I is abnormal.

label.value: elongated linear element

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form linear element that are longer than normal.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy at 5S rRNA genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at the portion of ribosomal DNA encoding 5S rRNA. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy at tRNA genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at tRNA genes. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: increased subtelomeric heterochromatin RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA derived from subtelomeric heterochromatin regions is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to subtelomeric heterochromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype the localization of a protein to heterochromatin in subtelomeric regions is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to TOP-53

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to TOP-53. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of TOP-53 that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal nucleosome occupancy at tRNA genes

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) at tRNA genes. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: increased histone H4-K12 acetylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 12 of histone H4 in centromere inner repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased heterochromatin assembly at subtelomere

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin assembly occurs to a lower extent than normal in subtelomeric regions. Heterochromatin assembly is the assembly of chromatin into a compact and highly condensed form that is often, but not always, transcriptionally silent.

label.value: increased H2A.Z level at subtelomere

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of the histone variant H2A.Z found associated with chromatin in subtelomeric regions is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: increased H2A.Z level at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of the histone variant H2A.Z found associated with chromatin in centromere inner repeat regions is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: normal protein level during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during mitosis is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein level during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein monoubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the monoubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein polyubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the polyubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased chromatin binding at centromere outer repeat

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) at the centromere outer repeat region is decreased.

label.value: normal chromatin binding at centromere outer repeat

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) at the centromere outer repeat region.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at the silent mating-type cassettes. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy at long terminal repeat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at long terminal repeat (LTR) regions. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: decreased protein level during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
